wp:term.wp:term_description:
Car parts with brief description

Gear lever

Used to change gears in a car.

Seat belt

A car has seat belts in the front and back. You use the verb fasten, when you put your seat belt. John fastened is seat belt before driving off.

Steering wheel

You use the steering wheel to control the direction of the car (steer the car).

Windscreen

The windscreen is the big window at the front of the car.

Windscreen wipers

Are the things used when it is raining, snowing or clean dirt of the windscreen. Head lights They are used when driving at night and when it is raining, snow or fog.

Tail lights

The lights that are at the back of the car are call lights. The orange light are called indicators and are used when the car is turning left or right. The white part is called the reverse light and lights up when the car is reversing backwards. The red part is used when the head lights are being used so other drivers can see the car in front of them at night time or poor driving conditions. It is also called a brake light and is used when the car is using the brake pedal.

Speedometer

The speedometer shows how fast the person driving the car is driving.

Fuel gauge

Used to Â show how much petrol or diesel the car has left

Temperature gauge

Shows how hot the cars engine is.

Car trip meter

This shows the driver how many miles the journey has took.

Rev counter

The rev counter is used to help you change gear and can be used for better fuel economy.

Alternators are typically found near the front of the engine and are driven by the crankshaft, which converts the pistons' up-and-down movement into circular movement. (To learn more about the basic parts of car engines, read How Car Engines Work.) Some early model vehicles used a separate drive belt from the crankshaft pulley to the alternator pulley, but most cars today have a serpentine belt, or one belt that drives all components that rely on crankshaft power. Most alternators are mounted using brackets that bolt to a specific point on the engine. One of the brackets is usually a fixed point, while the other is adjustable to tighten the drive belt.

What are car body panels made from?
The typical family sedan these days is usually made from steel body panels with plastic front and rear fascias. Some of them may have an aluminum hood and rear deck lid for weight savings. The unibody (the underlying frame) is almost always made from a combination of steel and special (and costly) high-strength steel.

[su_heading size="23" margin="10"]Company Mission and History[/su_heading]

  This is our local nelson business and we have been trying to help people with ages. Some people are interested in car parts to build their or to design their car, however to get the car parts they must go through different Car parts shops to obtain those parts needed for a car. Sometimes people are unable to get those car parts due to transportation. However, our main goal is to reach everyone in Nelson who needs car parts or auto parts and then to be delivered to their home at a very cheap cost. We provide all the services needed by the clients regarding auto parts. As more and more and people are trying to use online to get something, our job is to offer those people the services they require.

[su_heading size="23" margin="10"]Products and Services[/su_heading]

Our online business offers the customers a wide range of car parts from used to new, and then to deliver those parts to any place in Nelson at a very cheap price.

[su_heading size="23" margin="10"]Role[/su_heading]

The role of this website is to provide the customers the access to the list of items that we are going to offer, the car parts they are looking for, the model number, parts with picture representation, and the ability to choose used or new parts. After selecting the desired parts customers will get the opportunity to purchase the part online. This will allow the customers to order, pay, and to deliver the parts in their designated address. The customers can also choose delivery options from different list according to their interest. Our next purpose of the business will be promoting out business through customersâ rating and customersâ satisfaction which will be used later to improve and update our work accordingly. This change based on the customersâ review will not be immediate as we plan to do so when we have accumulated enough customersâ review. After that, we will try to extend our business not only locally, but also domestically across the country. This website will have soft, clean, and smooth rustic look that will convey a deep interest to the audience.

[su_heading size="23" margin="10"]Function[/su_heading]

The function of this website is to promote and sell car parts across Nelson at a cheap price fast and effectively.

[su_heading size="23" margin="10"]Internal[/su_heading]

We will make sure our website is simple and easy to use and the customers can go through our website with ease and efficiency and can look for items however they want it. We will create menu bar that will provide the requirements for the customers to find out whatever they are looking. Additionally, we will put our logo for Nelson Car parts that will direct them to the main page, if needed. We will also provide the customers with search tab that will help them to find out any car parts or car model they are looking for. We will try to make the website user friendly.

[su_heading size="23" margin="10"]External[/su_heading]

We feel like we can reach people across Nelson and later to other parts of New Zealand. I believe with the help of social media we can bring people closer to our website. Building these connections will benefit both me and them as they will get an effective and efficient service from us while they will they will be able to provide recommendations and links to our websites to others. "Auto Part Distributors across Nelson"

Â 

BNT Automotive

We are well connected with BNT NZ car parts limited. They have been our kind distributor for a long time and has been supporting us for long time.Â 

BNT Automotive has been a supplier to the New Zealand aftermarket for over 60 years. Today, no other automotive distributor offers the range or depth of products required to service such a diverse automotive aftermarket.

The companies foundations were built on manufacturing brake components for both the automotive trade and OEM operations in New Zealand. Today no other automotive supplier in New Zealand has the history and level of staff technical knowledge that BNT does. BNT prides itself on offering superior service to our customers and offering an extensive range of products that service New Zealands diverse automotive marketplace. With 54 branches BNT's geographic reach has stores located throughout all major centres over the country.

Relationships with our sister companies HCB batteries,Â Autolign SuspensionÂ and Truck & Trailer Parts give BNT even greater opportunity to completely service the New Zealand automotive trade.

BNT is a significant supplier of a wide range of automotive parts, accessories and engineering supplies to trade customers throughout New Zealand.

We are a growing business founded on quality products, value for money and superior service. Today, no other automotive distributor offers the range or depth of products required to service such a diverse automotive aftermarket.

BNT stocks a full range of brake, clutch, driveline, suspension, underbonnet, filters, oils, related products and service tools.

Young's Automotive

Youngs Automotive has been a vital part of the automotive parts supply chain in the top of the south and West Coast for over 35 years.

We took over this great company in February 2008.
We haveÂ four dedicated specialist salesmen with many years of experience in the automotive parts supply business.

We are a superior wholesaler/retailer supplying automotive, commercial and marine parts specializing in electrical components and accessories.
A lot of pride is taken in the expert advice we are able to offer putting us strides above our competitors and we can provide this as we have one qualified auto electrician and two ex-mechanicsÂ in our sales team.

We focus on Nelson, Marlborough, Golden Bay and the West Coast but this does not stop us servicing the whole of NZ as we can and will send our products Nationwide with very competitive freighting options available.

Youngs Automotive is an authorized dealer for leading and top quality brands such as Hella, Narva, VDO, Ryco and Fram. We are also a preferred supplier for Capricorn and Farmlands.

We strive to give every customer the service and advice they deserve and require, we are proud of our team for doing this day in and day out.Click edit button to change this text.
